## Implementation Plan

### Problem
Commits pushed directly to the repo (no associated PR) were always
routed to the 'Other' leftovers section of the changelog, even when
their commit title matched a category via `commit_patterns`. This made
the changelog less useful for repos that use direct pushes.

The version bump calculation was already correct — bump type is tracked
before the leftovers guard — so only the changelog display was broken.

### Root Cause
In `categorizeCommits()` (src/utils/changelog.ts), the leftovers guard:

    if (!categoryTitle || !raw.pr) {

The `|| !raw.pr` half forced ALL commits without a PR number into
leftovers, bypassing any category match that `matchCommitToCategory()`
had already found.

### Fix
Remove `|| !raw.pr` so the condition becomes:

    if (!categoryTitle) {

Only commits with no matching category go to leftovers.

### Why no other changes needed
- `createPREntriesFromRaw` already uses `raw.pr ?? ''`
- `formatChangelogEntry` already falls back to commit-hash links when
  `prNumber` is falsy (empty string)
- The `PullRequest.number` field is typed as `string`, not `string | null`,
  so an empty string is the correct sentinel for 'no PR'

### Tests
- Updated assertion in 'keeps commits without PR association' — commits
  now correctly land in 'Internal Changes' (via `chore:` pattern) instead
  of 'Other', so expected strings changed to title-cased versions.
- New test: 'categorizes direct commits (no PR) by commit_patterns'
- New test: 'mixes direct commits and PR commits in the same category'
